    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "An inordinate fondness for inconspicuous brown frogs: integration of phylogenomics, archival DNA analysis, morphology, and bioacoustics yields 24 new taxa in the subgenus Brygoomantis (genus Mantidactylus) from Madagascar" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441104>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441108>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441037> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441104>
    dc:description "FIGURE 36. Mantidactylus noralottae from the Isalo massif in life, in dorsolateral and ventral view. (a,b) Adult female (tissue ACZC 7948; FAZC 14340). (c,d) Adult male (tissue ACZC 7947; FAZC 14339)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7441104/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441108>
    dc:description "FIGURE 37. Audiospectrogram and corresponding oscillogram of a 1000 ms section of one advertisement call (call duration 2704 ms) of Mantidactylus noralottae, recorded 18 December 2004 at Ambovo, Isalo National Park (20°C air temperature). Recording bandpass-filtered at 1000–3500 Hz." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7441108/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441037>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Mantidactylus subgenus Brygoomantis species distribution based on verified records, divided by clade (Mantidactylus stelliger sp. nov. is presented alongside the inaudax clade for practicality). Colours for species correspond to those in Figs 2 and 4. Inset map shows the geographic regions of Madagascar identified by Boumans et al. (2007), referred to throughout the text." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7441037/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

